pr_body:
- **What kind of change does this PR introduce?** (Bug fix, feature, docs update, ...)
  Feature/Bug fix
- **What is the current behavior?** (You can also link to an open issue here)
  Pages children routes definition with parameter support are not working
- **What is the new behavior (if this is a feature change)?**
  Pages children routes definition with parameter support are working
  Additionally, it is possible to define route children without showing them in the sidebar
- **Other information**:

Adding the boolean parameter "dontShowChildren" to a pages route, it won't be shown in the sidebar. 
This makes possible children routes definition with parameter support, that previously wasn't working.
For example:

{
path: 'mypath',
component: MyComponent,
data: {
          menu: {myMenuData}
        },
        dontShowChildren:true,
        children: [
          { path: '', component: MyChildrenComponent },
          { path: ':id', component: MyChildComponent }
        ]
}

Because bootstrap4 introduces placeholder links https://github.com/twbs/bootstrap/issues/19402 , some of links we have in our admin panel without `href` attribute are being overrided by following css:

``` css
a:not([href]):not([tabindex]) {
  color: inherit;
  text-decoration: none;
}
```

This specifically breaks expand/collapse menuitems in sidebar and expand/collapse control in pageTop component in mint version.

* **What kind of change does this PR introduce?** (Bug fix, feature, docs update, ...)

A new feature - sidebar menu entries updating.

* **What is the current behavior?** (You can also link to an open issue here)

The sidebar menu is loaded at the beginning when _baSidebar.component_ is instantiated and remains unchanged since. It is also very hard to update it afterward.

* **What is the new behavior (if this is a feature change)?**

_baMenu.service_ is exposed to the application and via `updateMenuByRoutes`, which takes in the object of the type similar to _app.menu.ts_(essentially how the menu is structured), allows easy sidebar menu updating.

* **Other information**:

I believe this change does no harm and only provides benefits, as this feature was requested by a few people in issue #236.
If you have any questions, opinions or suggestions I would be happy to hear them.

To use this in a component/service of yours simply import `baMenu.service` from the _theme_ directory, inject it into the constructor of your component/service and use the `updateMenuByRoutes` method when the menu needs to be modified. You don't have to clone your menu, it will remain unchanged, opposed to the default behavior or _baMenu.service_ methods that mutate their inputs.

To test if this works you can modify the `constructor` of the _baMenu.service_:
``` typescript
  constructor(private _router:Router) {
    this.updateMenuByRoutes(<Routes>MENU);

    setInterval(() => {
      let menuPart = _.cloneDeep(MENU);
      menuPart[0].children = menuPart[0].children.filter(() => Math.random() > 0.5);
      console.log('Updating routes', menuPart);
      this.updateMenuByRoutes(<Routes>menuPart);
    }, 4000);
  }
```
Every 4 seconds the menu will be updated, items that should remain will be chosen randomly.

* **What kind of change does this PR introduce?** (Bug fix, feature, docs update, ...)

This PR was created in order to update the repository following the  [**style-guide**](https://angular.io/docs/ts/latest/guide/style-guide.html). The main changes are:

- All files had their names changed (camelCase to kebab-case). Ex: 'smartTables' to 'smart-tables';
- Components had their signature changed. Ex: 'App' now is 'AppComponent';
- Components/directives that uses the lifecycle hook methods (`OnInit, OnDestroy...`)  now **implements** them;
- Some simple changes, like including spaces between `import {Component}`,  and also in declaraction, like: `let x:number` (spaces after the **colon**);

